## Ontology Validation & Review workflow (Registry → My Tasks + Domain → Validation)

> Reconstructed from the codebase — the original verbatim entry was lost when an
> untracked `2026-06-08.log` was overwritten by a fast-forward pull.

**Context**: Business users needed a way to validate ontology versions: run soft
consistency checks, sign off through a review workflow, and keep an auditable trail
of who decided what. Built on top of the existing `DRAFT -> IN-REVIEW -> PUBLISHED`
version lifecycle (extend, not replace). Decisions: builder/admin can submit & publish,
any domain member can sign off, publish is **quorum**-gated (`review_quorum`), and the
consistency checks are advisory (**soft** gate). Every decision and lifecycle change is
persisted (with a status snapshot) to a new registry table.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/schema.sql` — new `domain_review_events`
   table (append-only audit log) with `actor`, `action`, `from_status`, `to_status`,
   `comment`, `meta`, `created_at` + `idx_review_events_domain_version`.
2. `src/back/objects/registry/store/base.py` — `ReviewEvent` TypedDict and the
   `record_review_event` / `list_review_events` / `list_all_review_events` abstract
   methods on `RegistryStore`.
3. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py` — Lakebase implementation +
   `_ensure_review_events_table()` self-heal (mirrors the `build_runs` pattern);
   `domain_review_events` added to `_KNOWN_TABLES`.
4. `src/back/objects/registry/RegistryService.py` — thin wrappers delegating to the store.
5. `src/back/objects/registry/ReviewService.py` (new) — stateless workflow orchestrator:
   `my_tasks`, `review_detail`, `submit`, `signoff`, `publish`, `reopen` plus helpers
   (`_summarize`, `_pending_actions`, `_resolve_roles`, quorum/role checks). Approvals reset
   on resubmit / change-request / publish.
6. `src/back/objects/registry/__init__.py` — lazy `ReviewService` export via `__getattr__`
   to avoid a registry↔session import cycle.
7. `src/api/routers/internal/review.py` (new) + `__init__.py` — `/review` router:
   `GET /my-tasks`, `GET /{folder}/{version}`, and POST `submit|signoff|publish|reopen`,
   resolving the caller's role against the *target* domain.
8. `src/front/config/menu_config.json` — Registry → Review → "My Tasks" and Domain →
   "Validation" menu items.
9. `src/front/templates/registry.html` + `partials/registry/_registry_my_tasks.html` (new)
   + `static/registry/js/registry-my-tasks.js` (new) + css — cross-domain worklist with
   context-aware actions.
10. `src/front/templates/domain.html` + `partials/domain/_domain_review.html` (new) +
    `static/domain/js/domain-review.js` (new) + css, wired via `domain.js` — per-version
    Validation workspace: status banner with quorum progress, soft consistency-check summary
    (`/validate/detailed`), action buttons, and the audit timeline.
11. Tests: `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py` (new),
    `tests/units/registry/test_registry_store.py` (review-event round-trips),
    `tests/units/api/test_review_endpoints.py` (new).
12. Docs: `README.md` + `docs/user-guide.md` — Validation & Review workflow section.

**Test result**: full `tests/units` suite green (review service, store, and endpoint tests pass).

