## Review comments — per-transition comment prompt + chat-style history viewer

**Context**: The review/validation workflow already persists a `comment` on every event
(`domain_review_events`), but the UI only collected one on sign-off; all other status switches
(submit / publish / reopen) went through a plain confirm dialog with no note, and there was no
way to read the full comment thread from the worklists. This adds a comment popup to *every*
status switch and a chat-style "all comments" viewer reachable from the task lists.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/js/review-modals.js` (new) — shared `window.ReviewModals` helper,
   loaded globally. `promptComment(opts)` returns a `Promise<{confirmed, comment}>` (confirm
   dialog with an attached, optionally-required comment textarea); `showComments(folder, version)`
   fetches `/review/{folder}/{version}` and renders the full event history as chat bubbles
   (actor avatar, action label, `from -> to` transition chip, timestamp, comment body).
2. `src/front/static/global/css/review-modals.css` (new) — styling for the chat bubbles/avatars,
   using existing `--db-*` custom properties.
3. `src/front/templates/base.html` — load the shared CSS (after `help-modal.css`) and the shared
   JS (after `utils.js`, defer) so all three surfaces (home, registry, domain) share one impl.
4. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-review.js` — submit / publish / reopen now open
   `ReviewModals.promptComment` (comment persisted to the audit trail); approve / request-changes
   reuse the same prompt (request-changes requires a comment). Removed the bespoke in-page
   sign-off modal wiring (`openSignoffModal` / `submitSignoff` / `signoffModal`).
5. `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_review.html` — removed the now-unused
   `#reviewSignoffModal` markup.
6. `src/front/static/registry/js/registry-my-tasks.js` and
   `src/front/static/home/js/home-tasks.js` — added a per-row "comments" button
   (`ReviewModals.showComments`) and switched the inline `transition()` from `showConfirmDialog`
   to `ReviewModals.promptComment`, forwarding the typed comment in the POST body.
7. `src/api/routers/internal/review.py` — import `ReviewService` directly from its submodule
   (`back.objects.registry.ReviewService`) instead of the lazily re-exported package attribute,
   removing a test-collection-order fragility (the submodule name shadowed the re-exported class).
8. `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py` — added comment-persistence tests for every
   status switch (`test_submit_persists_comment`, `test_signoff_approve_persists_comment`,
   `test_signoff_request_changes_persists_comment`, `test_publish_persists_comment`,
   `test_reopen_persists_comment`) plus `test_review_detail_surfaces_events_with_comments`
   (the data source for the chat viewer).
9. `tests/units/api/test_ui_rendering.py` — added `test_review_modals_assets_loaded` asserting the
   shared `review-modals.js` / `review-modals.css` are wired into base.html on every page.

