## Per-domain review sign-off quorum

**Context**: The review **sign-off quorum** (how many distinct approvals are required before an
IN-REVIEW version can be published) was a single registry-wide value stored in `global_config`
under `review_quorum`, with no UI to change it. It should instead be a **per-domain** policy,
set when a domain is created and editable on the Domain Information / Global page. Decision:
store it as a typed column on the `domains` table (domain-scoped, one value for all versions),
default `1`; no backfill of the old global key (it becomes dead).

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/schema.sql` — added `review_quorum integer NOT NULL
   DEFAULT 1 CHECK (review_quorum >= 1)` to the `domains` table.
2. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py` — new `_ensure_domains_review_quorum_column()`
   lazy self-heal migration (mirrors the `status` column pattern); `get_domain_quorum(folder)`;
   `read_version` now returns `info.review_quorum`; `write_version` persists the column from
   `info.review_quorum` in the `domains` UPSERT; `list_domains_with_metadata` returns
   `review_quorum` per domain.
3. `src/back/objects/registry/store/base.py` — added abstract `get_domain_quorum(folder)` and
   `review_quorum` to the `DomainSummary` TypedDict.
4. `src/back/objects/registry/ReviewService.py` — `_quorum(svc, folder)` now reads the per-domain
   value (`store.get_domain_quorum`); `my_tasks` resolves quorum per-domain from the domain list
   and no longer returns a single top-level `quorum`; `review_detail`/`publish` pass the folder;
   removed the dead `_QUORUM_KEY` global-config constant.
5. `src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py` — `get_empty_domain`, `export_for_save`, and
   `import_from_file` now carry `review_quorum` (default 1, clamped >= 1).
6. `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py` — `save_domain_info` accepts/clamps `review_quorum`
   (new `_coerce_quorum` helper); `get_domain_info` and `get_domain_template_data` expose it.
7. `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_information.html` — new "Sign-off quorum" number
   input on the Global tab.
8. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain.js` — `loadDomainInfo`/`saveDomainInfo` load and send
   `review_quorum`.
9. `src/front/static/global/js/navbar.js` — `saveDomainInfoBeforeSave` includes `review_quorum`
   so it persists to the registry on save-to-uc.
10. `src/front/static/registry/js/registry-my-tasks.js` — dropped the now-unused global `quorum`
    render argument (each task already carries its own `required`).
11. `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py` — mock `store.get_domain_quorum` instead of
    `load_global_config`.
12. `tests/units/registry/test_registry_store.py` — `_InMemoryStore.get_domain_quorum`.
13. `tests/units/domain/test_domain_service.py` — quorum save/clamp/default tests.
14. `README.md`, `docs/user-guide.md` — quorum documented as per-domain (Domain → Information →
    Global).

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/schema.sql`
- `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py`
- `src/back/objects/registry/store/base.py`
- `src/back/objects/registry/ReviewService.py`
- `src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py`
- `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`
- `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_information.html`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain.js`
- `src/front/static/global/js/navbar.js`
- `src/front/static/registry/js/registry-my-tasks.js`
- `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py`
- `tests/units/registry/test_registry_store.py`
- `tests/units/domain/test_domain_service.py`
- `README.md`
- `docs/user-guide.md`

**Test result**: `pytest tests/units` -> 2242 passed, 15 skipped.

**Migration note**: existing Lakebase deployments self-heal the new column on first read/write
(`ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS`, owner-aware). Because the `domains` table already exists,
`schema.sql`'s `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` does NOT add the column on redeploy, so the
deploy-time migration was added to `scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh`
(`ALTER TABLE domains ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS review_quorum integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 1`,
run as the schema owner). Run `make bootstrap-lakebase` to apply it to an already-deployed
instance. The old registry-wide `review_quorum` in `global_config` is no longer read.

> Deployed to `fe-vm-bcayla-demos` (apps `ontobricks-050` + `mcp-ontobricks-050`) on 2026-06-09;
> Lakebase `domains.review_quorum` migration applied; both apps RUNNING, UI `/healthz` 200.

