## Admin can publish regardless of the sign-off quorum

**Context**: Publishing an IN-REVIEW version was gated by the sign-off quorum for everyone,
including admins. Admins should be able to drive any lifecycle transition — including publish —
without being blocked by the quorum, so a domain is never stuck waiting on sign-offs.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/objects/registry/ReviewService.py` — new `_is_admin(user_role, user_domain_role)`
   helper (app-level OR domain-level admin). `publish` now bypasses the quorum check for admins
   and records `quorum_override` in the `published` event meta. `review_detail` returns
   `can_publish` for admins even when the quorum is not met, plus a top-level `publish_override`
   flag. `_pending_actions` (My Tasks) surfaces the Publish action for admins below quorum.
2. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-review.js` — when `publish_override` is set, the Validation
   panel shows an "Admin override" warning and a `Publish (override quorum)` button.
3. `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py` — `test_publish_blocked_until_quorum` now uses a
   non-admin builder; added `test_publish_admin_overrides_quorum`,
   `test_publish_domain_admin_overrides_quorum`, `test_pending_actions_builder_no_publish_below_quorum`,
   `test_pending_actions_admin_publish_below_quorum`, `test_review_detail_admin_can_publish_below_quorum`.
4. `README.md`, `docs/user-guide.md` — documented the admin quorum override.

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/objects/registry/ReviewService.py`
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-review.js`
- `tests/units/registry/test_review_service.py`
- `README.md`
- `docs/user-guide.md`

**Test result**: `pytest tests/units` -> 2247 passed, 15 skipped. `node --check` clean.

