## Fix: version filter dropdowns disabled on read-only domains (Runs / Audit trail)

**Context**: On a read-only domain version (status IN-REVIEW or PUBLISHED, or an older/inactive
version → `body.read-only-version`), the **Version** filter `<select>` on **Domain → Runs** and
**Domain → Audit trail** was greyed out and unusable. Those dropdowns only filter a read-only
timeline by version — they don't mutate anything — so they must stay interactive for readers.

**Root cause**: The catch-all read-only gate in `permissions.css` disables every `<select>` except
an explicit allow-list (`#domainVersionSelect`, `#loadDomainSelect`, `#loadVersionSelect`). The
two filters (`#auditVersionFilter`, `#runsVersionFilter`) weren't listed, and the sibling
`[id*="filter"]` input exemption is case-sensitive (lowercase), so it would not have matched the
capital-F ids regardless.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css` — added `:not(#auditVersionFilter)` and
   `:not(#runsVersionFilter)` to the read-only `select` gate, and documented them in the
   exemption-list comment.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css`

**Test result**: CSS-only change; no test suite impact.

